summary: FALCON DOORS DO NOT ALWAYS OPEN CORRECTLY.  SOMETIMES THEY SENSE AN OBSTACLE THAT IS NOT PRESENT AND SO WILL NOT OPEN.  THIS FAILURE HAPPENS MORE OFTEN WHEN THE FALCON DOORS ARE HOT, FOR EXAMPLE AFTER BEING IN THE SUN.  TESLA SERVICE CENTER HAS REPLACED THE SENSORS IN BOTH OF MY FALCON DOORS, BUT THE PROBLEM REMAINS.
